results.name: a(n) = number of divisors d of n which are either 1 or of the form Product_(i) (p_i^e_i) where the e_i are <= 1.
comment: a(n) = number of non-powerful divisors d of n where powerful numbers are numbers from A001694(m) for m >=1.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
Index entries for sequences computed from exponents in factorization of n
formula: a(1) = 1, a(p) = 2, a(pq) = 4, a(pq...z) = 2^k, a(p^k) = 2, for p, q = primes, k = natural numbers, pq...z = product of k (k > 2) distinct primes p, q, ..., z.
example: For n = 12, set of such divisors is {1, 2, 3, 6, 12}; a(12) = 5.
